Bayesian Approaches to the Interpretation of CMIP Data

This repository contains Bayesian modeling utilities and illustrative notebooks to interpret CMIP data under varying statistical assumptions and structural heterogeneity across models.

Structure
root/
├── modeling/
│   ├── bayes.py
│   └── viz.py
└── notebooks/
    ├── T2000.ipynb
    ├── ECS.ipynb
    └── Process.ipynb
modeling/bayes.py — functions for Bayesian model fitting
modeling/viz.py — graphical utilities for posterior visualization
Notebooks
T2000.ipynb
Fixed vs. random effects formulations illustrated using temperature anomaly in the year 2000.
ECS.ipynb
Uncorrelated vs. correlated random effects in the estimation of equilibrium climate sensitivity, including the incorporation of emergent constraints.
Process.ipynb
Interpretation of CMIP output when Earth System Models differ in the inclusion of a given process.
Scope

The examples emphasize:

* hierarchical (random effects) formulations
* dependence structures across models
* incorporation of external constraints
* treatment of structural differences across ESMs

Usage

Open the notebooks in notebooks/ to reproduce the analyses. The modeling/ module provides supporting functionality for estimation and visualization.